{"id":"quant-ph/0309058","submitter":"Hugues de Riedmatten","authors":"Hugues de Riedmatten, Ivan Marcikic, Valerio Scarani, Wolfgang Tittel,\n  Hugo Zbinden and Nicolas Gisin","title":"Tailoring photonic entanglement in high-dimensional Hilbert spaces","comments":"4 pages, 4 figures, published version","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. A 69, 050304 (2004)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevA.69.050304","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":null,"abstract":"  We present an experiment where two photonic systems of arbitrary dimensions\ncan be entangled. The method is based on spontaneous parametric down conversion\nwith trains of d pump pulses with a fixed phase relation, generated by a\nmode-locked laser. This leads to a photon pair created in a coherent\nsuperposition of $d$ discrete emission times, given by the successive laser\npulses. Entanglement is shown by performing a two-photon interference\nexperiment and by observing the visibility of the interference fringes\nincreasing as a function of the dimension d. Factors limiting the visibility,\nsuch as the presence of multiple pairs in one train, are discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 5 Sep 2003 14:53:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 15 Sep 2004 18:14:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
